Passengers travelling the full length of the route (Parramatta to Sutherland), will need to change buses at Bankstown.
  • 920 services depart from Bankstown Station Stand E
  • 960 services depart from Bankstown Station Stand B
All other stops remain the same.
 
For more information see the news story.
 
This change will improve journey time and reliability for passengers and will allow drivers to complete other routes impacted by driver shortages.
 
Plan your trip with Trip Planner or transport apps before you travel.

urlText: Major Event Buses operating for Taylor Swift concerts at Olympic Park 23 - 26 Feb
content:
Major Event Buses will run for Taylor Swift | The Eras Tour on Friday 23, Saturday 24, Sunday 25 and Monday 26 February 2024.
 
Travel on Major Event Buses is included in the cost of tickets to Taylor Swift | The Eras Tour concerts only, ticketholders do not need to tap on and off, simply show your ticket to the driver when boarding buses.
 
Buses run every 5 to 20 minutes, subject to traffic conditions. Timetables are designed to accommodate Taylor Swift | The Eras Tour show times, and crowd arrivals and departures.
 
Note, buses will not leave Olympic Park until the Taylor Swift concert has finished each night, expected from approximately 11pm. Passengers boarding services prior to the end of the show will need to wait until the concert has finished before the bus departs.
